---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How to Help"
  description="Volunteer, donate, or connect with the Nameless Cemetery Association. Help preserve a historic Texas cemetery."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <h1>How to Help</h1>
      <p class="page-intro">
        Nameless Cemetery is maintained entirely by volunteers. Whether you have family here,
        live nearby, or simply care about preserving Texas history, there are meaningful ways
        to contribute.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container--narrow">

      <h2 data-reveal>Volunteer</h2>
      <div class="photo-grid" data-reveal>
        <figure class="photo-grid-item">
          <img src="/images/tractor-wide.jpeg" alt="Volunteer grounds work at Nameless Cemetery" loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
        <figure class="photo-grid-item">
          <img src="/images/tractor-cab-pov.jpeg" alt="View from inside the tractor cab during grounds work" loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
      </div>
      <p>
        Grounds work is the most immediate need. Mowing, trimming, fence repair, headstone
        cleaning, and general upkeep keep the cemetery accessible and respectful. We organize
        work days before major events and as seasonal needs arise.
      </p>
      <div class="callout">
        <p>
          <strong>Next work day:</strong> Early April 2026 (date TBD), in preparation for the
          April 18 Return to Nameless event. If you'd like to help,
          <a href="mailto:info@namelesscemetery.org">reach out</a> and let us know.
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="volunteer-feature">
        <img src="/images/volunteer-tractor.jpeg" alt="Volunteer working alongside a tractor at Nameless Cemetery" loading="lazy" />
      </figure>

      <h2 data-reveal>To Make a Donation</h2>
      <p>
        Donations support mowing costs, fence repair, headstone restoration, and long-term
        preservation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Donations can be made by check made out to Nameless Cemetery Assoc. and mailed to:
      </p>
      <div class="donation-address">
        <p>
          Mark Manley<br/>
          21401 Cherryhollow Cove<br/>
          Leander, TX 78641
        </p>
      </div>
      <figure class="photo-feature">
        <img src="/images/cemetery-wide.jpeg" alt="Nameless Cemetery grounds with lawnmower under live oak trees" loading="lazy" />
      </figure>

      <h2 data-reveal>Share What You Know</h2>
      <p>
        If your family has connections to Nameless Cemetery or the Nameless community, your
        stories and records matter. Old photos, letters, family Bibles, burial records, and
        oral history all help build a more complete picture of the people buried here.
      </p>
      <p>
        We are especially interested in:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Photos of headstones, the cemetery, or the community (any era)</li>
        <li>Family genealogy records connecting to burials at Nameless</li>
        <li>Stories about the Nameless community, the schoolhouse, or the families here</li>
        <li>Corrections or additions to our burial records</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Please <a href="mailto:info@namelesscemetery.org?subject=Nameless%20Cemetery%20History">contact us</a>
        with your stories. Every detail helps preserve the record.
      </p>

      <h2 data-reveal>Attend an Event</h2>
      <p>
        The annual meeting (first Saturday in October) and community events at the Nameless
        Schoolhouse are the best way to connect with the association and meet other families
        with ties to this place.
      </p>

      <h2 data-reveal>Spread the Word</h2>
      <p>
        Follow us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/NamelessCemetery" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook</a>
        and share our posts. If you know someone with family connections to Nameless Cemetery,
        point them our way. Many descendants don't know the association exists.
      </p>
      <p>
        Also follow
        <a href="https://www.facebook.com/FriendsofNamelessSchool" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Friends of Nameless School</a>,
        the nonprofit that preserves the historic 1909 schoolhouse next door. The school and cemetery
        share the same land and the same community.
      </p>

      <h2 data-reveal>Contact</h2>
      <div class="contact-card" data-reveal>
        <h3>Nameless Cemetery Association</h3>
        <p>23426 Nameless Road<br/>Leander, TX 78641</p>
        <p>
          <a href="mailto:info@namelesscemetery.org">info@namelesscemetery.org</a>
        </p>
        <div class="officers">
          <h4>Officers</h4>
          <p>President: Carolyn Bonnet - <a href="mailto:carolynbonnet@gmail.com">carolynbonnet@gmail.com</a></p>
          <p>Treasurer: Mark Manley - <a href="mailto:manleymachining@yahoo.com">manleymachining@yahoo.com</a></p>
        </div>
        <p>
          <a href="https://www.facebook.com/NamelessCemetery" target="_blank" rel="noopener">facebook.com/NamelessCemetery</a>
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/3528/nameless-cemetery" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Find a Grave: Nameless Cemetery</a>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding-top: var(--space-3xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sandstone);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-intro {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--patina);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .contact-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--sandstone);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .contact-card h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .contact-card p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
  }

  .officers {
    margin-block: var(--space-md);
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--sandstone);
  }

  .officers h4 {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--patina);
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .donation-address {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--sandstone);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    margin-block: var(--space-md);
  }

  .donation-address p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Volunteer feature */
  .volunteer-feature {
    margin-block: var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
  }

  .volunteer-feature img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .volunteer-selfie {
    text-align: center;
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    overflow: visible;
  }

  .volunteer-selfie img {
    width: auto;
    max-width: 140px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    border-radius: 50%;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15));
  }

  .volunteer-feature figcaption {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--patina);
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  /* Photos */
  .photo-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-block: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .photo-grid-item {
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .photo-grid-item img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .photo-feature {
    margin-block: var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .photo-feature img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .photo-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
